- PRINCIPLES FOR FINDING MONTHLY DEFENSE EXPENDITURE DATA:
- 1. TIMING OF DATA PUBLICATION: Monthly expenditure data for period X appears in bulletins published AFTER period X. For calendar year data, look at bulletins from the following year. January data appears in March bulletins, December data in June bulletins (pre-1976).
- 2. IDENTIFYING THE RIGHT TABLE: Look for "Cash Income and Outgo" tables for cash-based figures or "Expenditures by Major Classifications"/"Budget Receipts and Expenditures" tables for budgetary figures. The structure changes over time: pre-WWII uses simpler categories, post-WWII has more detailed breakdowns.

