**From officeqa-uid0033:**
- PRINCIPLES FOR TREASURY BULLETIN ANALYSIS:
- 1. PUBLICATION TIMING: Treasury Bulletins are published monthly and contain data from the PREVIOUS month. A March 1977 bulletin contains February 1977 data. To find March 1977 data, look in the April 1977 bulletin.
- 2. RATE TABLE LOCATION: Treasury bill rates are found in Table PDO-2 "Offerings of Bills" (comprehensive) and also in the narrative "13-Week and 26-Week Bills" section (summary). The PDO-2 table provides the most complete and precise data.

